args: How far did Lea and Emma wander\nin their search for Forte?
Oh, those two are a scrappy pairâ€”\nI'm sure they'll be juuust fine.\nYou can relax about that.

More pressing is our plan to deal with the
Lord of the Skies. Per the theory, if we
draw on the power in the mana fount, the
procedure we tried earlier should work.
But the fly in the ointment is how long\nit's going to take to see that little plan\nthrough to its conclusion.
And how we even lure her all the way\nout here in the first place.
Looks like we won't need to worry\nabout that.

So much black mana... It's a wonder
this girl is even alive! I'd wager her
poor mind is little more than a gaggle
of bats in a belfry now.
I'll fight to buy us timeâ€”\nyou ready the magic!
O ye who preside over laws of the abyss!\nO mana, replete in this fell land!\nSwirl, take form, and become a cage!
Now, all of you!\nActivate the sealing barrier!
Forgive me for foregoing a frontal assault.\nYou're a bit of a hot potato right now,\nso we opted to lock you up instead.
That barrier comes from our combined\nstrength; it won't be broken so easily\nas all that.
*pant* And now if Forte tries to break\nfree of the wall and uses up all of the\nblack mana...
She should return to her senses, yes.\nThough really, there's only about a \nfifty-fifty chance of that. ...Hrk!
I warned you this wouldn't be some\nstroll down the boardwalk, kiddo!
Our magic has its limits, which means\nthe question is whether the black mana\ngives out first...or we do...
Oh, I'll answer that question for you:\nYou're all going to die right now.
Are you kidding me?! Why is the\nimperial army showing up NOW?!

Hold still, you traitorous prince!
Any sudden moves, and I will separate
the heads of these two lovely ladies
from the rest of their bodies.
I am SO sorry about this!
Enough talk! Drop your weapons or I will\nslay your comrades where they stand.
Ignore them! There's no need to worry\nabout us!

Aaah ha ha! To think we have the Empire's
most wanted criminal unarmed and weak
like a fish in a barrel! But the question is,
ï¼‚sire,ï¼‚ how shall we gut you...?
Ah, I know. You there! Mages!\nLower the barrier around that knight.
Uh, sir? Is that really a good idea?\nShouldn't we just kill 'em instead?

They're clearly afraid of that woman,
which should prove quite interesting.
I think we've earned the right for a little
entertainment, don't you?
I am the Lord of the Skies...\nI seek to crush everything...
You will serve as a flagstone\non my path of conquest, Prince!
Kill him! Kill the prince!\nKIIIILL HIIIIIM!
Anyone can defeat an enemy,\nbut true victory is different.

Only someone who boldly faces a foe
head-on can do that! Only one who
wields not just strength, but HONOR,
can hope to do that!
I told you to be SILENT!
The black mana uses you to its own ends,\njust as these blackguards seek to do!\nYou can find no victory here!
Answer me, Forte! Who are you?! \nWhat is it you seek?!
You're spoiling the fun, you wretch!
Enough of this! Kill the fiend-hating rebel!\nOne hostage will serve our purposes\nas well as two, after all.
I am the Lord of the Skies...
I confront and defeat strong warriors!\nFor that reason alone does my lance shine!
...Fascinating. I can't believe she\nshook off the effects of that much\nblack mana all on her own.
Still, this provides satisfying verification.\nWe can now move on to our next step.
I must offer my apologies for the rudeness\nI have incurred upon you. But first...
Right. Let's knock some sense into these\nunderhanded imperial goons.
Huh. Perhaps this wasn't the finest\nidea I've ever had. ...Oh well!\nBring out the secret weapon, men!

Surprised, are you? This is our force of
selectively bred fiendsâ€”the strongest
anywhere! You will fall before them
like chaff beneath the farmer's scythe!
You would deign name something\nï¼‚strongestï¼‚ while standing before\nthe Lord of the Skies?
Well enough. Let us see just how strong\nthese beasts of yours are.
A fair fight! Strength against strength!
